title: For Sale:  ISSC Mk22 SCAR-style .22
postcontent: ISSC Mk22 with 20 round mag. I bought it a few years ago, and it has sat in my safe unfired. I finally put 60 rounds through it the other day, and at 50 yards it makes nice groups. The internals of the Mk22 rifles are the same as the GSG-522 MP5 style .22's. So the tricks and mods for those work on these. I was all in the tacti-cool 22 thing at one point, but that was then and this is now. The stock folds too, and is adjustable. These type rifles like high or hyper velocity ammo. You can shoot the standard velocity bulk stuff in it, but you may get a few FTF or FTE if you go that route. I shot one mag of SV and it did fine except for one FTF. With HV not one problem.You can get mags and parts easily. I have already done the screw upgrade kit for the bolt assembly. The optic is a Firefield brand and works well for plinking at the range. I moved here a few months ago, and I don't shoot as much as anymore since I don't have property like before. Cash is nice, or if you have a bolt action 22 in good condition or a bolt action centerfire that is functional but may need some clean-up an even trade works too. I'm in Moses Lake, but travel to Kennewick. I can also do Wenatchee or Spokane.
